Industrial systems with annual energy consumption over 3 000 MWh are required to have their energy efficiency audited every three years. The prescribed measures are mandatory. Energy Efficiency for Competitive Industry is a new programme that provides low-interest loans to small and medium-sized enterprises. The total amount of funds under the programme is €300 mln.. €150 million of this amount will be provided by Operational Program Competitiveness and the remaining amount -from European Bank for Reconstruction and Development credit lines through the Bulgarian commercial banks.
_x000D_Eligible projects for funding are, for example:
_x000D_• New co-generation plants for thermal and electric energy;
_x000D_• Rehabilitation of boiler aggregates/boilers, improved thermal insulation, etc.;
_x000D_• Replacement of old boiler aggregates with condensing boilers;
_x000D_• Switching from electricity heating to heating based on direct burning of fuels;
_x000D_• Improvement of technological processes, including improved control and management;
_x000D_• Reconstruction of steam distribution systems, installation of steam traps, increasing the efficiency of the condensate recovery process, etc.;
_x000D_• Building of new or reconstruction of existing plants for heat recovery from processes – so called “utilizators”;
_x000D_• Installation of absorption chillers;
_x000D_• Installation of variable speed drive motors;
_x000D_• Reconstruction of compressed air systems - so called compressor installations;
_x000D_• Reconstruction of power distribution systems;
_x000D_• Introduction of systems for energy management of production or of offices and other buildings, etc.

_x000D_Large industrial enterprises will be financed under the green industry procedure of Operational Program Competitiveness.

The scheme is aimed to foster green economic development in Hungary by implementing environmental programs related to energy efficiency and renewable energy sources using revenues from selling the country’s Kyoto Units. The scheme can offer funding for the following purposes:
_x000D_a)	research, innovation and demonstration projects in the field of emission reduction and adaptation for the consequences of climate change;
_x000D_b)	energy production from renewable energy sources and the improvement of energy efficiency;
_x000D_c)	support of transition for low emission transport and public transport ;
_x000D_d)	to fund the 50% of the national contribution to the Green Climate Fund;
_x000D_e)	costs of the operation of the scheme.

Reducing the emissions of the waste sector through a variety of actions including: 
_x000D_- Recycling;
_x000D_- Reducing organic waste landfill deposition;
_x000D_- Definition of a GHG emission reduction target for 2020 and corresponding intermediate targets;
_x000D_- Green taxation reform including changes in the waste management tax and introduction of a fee on lightweight plastic bags;
_x000D_- Promoting the substitution of fossil fuels by Fuel Derived from Waste (CDR) produced from municipal waste;
_x000D_- Promoting the use of compost produced by the treatment of municipal waste;
_x000D_- Increased recovery and use of biogas in municipal waste treatment facilities;
_x000D_- Promoting the use of biofuels from used cooking oils;
_x000D_- Limit waste production through an absolute decrease of the amount of waste produced in relation to a reference level (waste prevention actions targeted to industry, services and consumers)

Bans and duties (that have effect on projected emissions) include:
_x000D_• bans of bringing certain new equipment on the market;
_x000D_• the service ban for F-gases with GWP 2500 and more;
_x000D_• duty of collecting the gases from decommissioned equipment;
_x000D_• certification duties for enterpreneurs who are handling the F-gases.

Le règlement n° 517/2014 (dit « F-Gas II ») du 16 avril 2014 prévoit :
_x000D_-	un mécanisme de réduction progressive des quantités de HFC exprimées en équivalent CO2 mises sur le marché via un système de quotas ;
_x000D_-	des interdictions de mise sur le marché de produits et d’équipements contenant des gaz à effet de serre fluorés dépassant un certain PRG ;
_x000D_-	l’interdiction de maintenance des installations de réfrigération avec des fluides de PRG supérieur à 2500 à partir du 1er janvier 2020.

